6:
Oh gosh... It's so... unbelievably
hot...
I'm definitely going to melt by the
end of this.
14:
Thank you...
Man, I even went through the trouble
of upgrading the heat resistance
effect on my clothes too...
19:
Are you sure you're in good enough
health to do this? The ruins we're to
explore today are said to be on the
safer side, but if you're not feeling
well...
24:
No way, they said that once we get
into the ruins, it'll be a breeze!
Nothing to worry about.
31: In what world is this a BREEZE?!
41:
Quite odd for a trap to still be active.
According to those hunters, these
ruins are supposed to have been
thoroughly excavated already.
46:
Yeah... Also, it's weird that only
Denah got caught in the trap.
52:
No kidding! It's like I'm the only one
playing on hard mode or something.
70:
Letters? How about it, Denah? Can
you read what they say?
75:
Hmm... Let's see... This inscription
appears to be... a warning?
78:
"Those who covet forbidden power
are condemned to die."
What?!
87: Lend me your aid, my Lord!
95:
I-I think so... You seriously saved our
butts there.
104:
I saw my whole life flash before my
eyes there for a moment...
107:
This must be the innermost section
of the ruins. Why would the trap
door lead to a place like this?
118:
Does that just scream "trap" to
anyone else?
126: Looks like we're not alone here...
131:
This room was merely another part
of the trap... This isn't good. We must
find a way out!
135: Don't worry. I'll take care of this.
141:
Throw as many enemies at me as
you want, I'll destroy them all!
145:
There's something wrong... That
power... It's not normal!
165:
Denah! Are you okay? 
Can you hear us?
169:
Mortals...
Your bodies... So ephemeral and
frail...
178:
None escape my gaze...
I am witness... to all creation...
184:
Just stop! We don't care what you
have to say—just give us Denah
back!
194: Stop, Denah! This isn't like you!
214:
No! No, no, no, no, no!
This is WRONG!
218:
Stop it... 
Even if you are my Lord, I can't...
222:
I can't let you hurt my friends!
I won't allow it!
227:
Denah... Thank goodness you've
returned to your senses!
236:
Haha... That's right, it's regular old
me! Hold that thought, please—
I need to take care of the rest of
these guys!
239: Stay back where it's safe, everyone!
243:
How dare you lay a hand on my
friends!
254:
I'm so sorry for screwing things up,
everyone...
257:
I... I was able to keep my memories
this time. I remember.
259:
My Lord possessed my body and...
tried to kill Alk.
263:
Apologizing won't undo what I did... 
If you want me to, I…
278:
We, uh... We're about to go pick a
fight with literal gods, you know.
281:
We'll need all the help we can get to
do that. Having abilities like the ones
you just demonstrated could come
in handy.
283:
I definitely agree that this... Lord of
yours is bad news, but... If we use
him correctly, he could be our trump
card.
287: Let's go back to Starview Village.
298:
But I must ask you to keep a strong
hold on these powers of yours,
Denah. There's no guarantee you'll
be able to stop yourself next time.
303:
You're right. I... I'll do my best!
I'll face the Lord head on and get
him to see things my way!
306: I swear this! Let this be our covenant!
310:
No matter what happens...
I will always be your friend!
